<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LLOYD, VENTURA HAND MOORPARK 3RD CONSECUTIVE LOSS, 6-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RALPH NICHOLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Darren Lloyd's two-run double in the sixth inning snapped a 2-2 tie and lifted 
Ventura College to a 6-2 Western State Conference win over visiting Moorpark on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark also threatened in the sixth, but sophomore right-hander Shane Espitia 
struck out Dan Smith with the bases loaded and the Raiders came away scoreless. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura added two runs in the seventh on a single, an error, David Eggert's 
scoring fly ball and a wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
John Chiaramonte (5-3) gave up nine hits and five runs to suffer the loss as 
the Raiders (20-13, 9-7 in conference play) lost their third game in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Espitia (6-2) gave up two runs and six hits to pick up the win for Ventura 
(25-8, 13-3). RALPH NICHOLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
