<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta 9, Pierce 0 -- Pierce starter Mike Stephenson surrendered four runs in 3 
1/3 innings and last-place Cuesta (3-12 in conference play) upset the Brahmas 
in a WSC game at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 6, Cal Lutheran 3 -- The Vanguards scored four 
times in the fifth inning to rally in the Golden State Athletic Conference game 
at Southern California College. Doug Rystrom (6-2) went the distance, striking 
out two and walking three. 
</P>
<P>
Mission 8, East L.A. 2 -- Mission ended the Southern California Athletic 
Conference game at Valley College with a triple play. 
</P>
<P>
Right fielder Chris Romo snared Dan Beel's line drive and fired to shortstop 
Albert Torres to nab Jose Monchiez off second base. Torres then completed the 
play by relaying to the plate to retire Dan Lenone trying to score from third. 
</P>
<P>
Westmont 11, The Master's 7 -- Westmont (24-13) held off a late rally to win 
the nonconference game at Master's. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 8, Valley 5 -- Chico Garcia tripled in two runs in the seventh 
inning to lift Santa Monica to a WSC win over visiting Valley. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 3-0, UC Riverside 0-1 -- In the opener, Northridge 
freshman Heather Lindstrom (15-4) threw a six-hitter, struck out four and 
walked none in a California Collegiate Athletic Assn. game at UC Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
In the second game, Debbie Dickmann was hurt by a first-inning error as 
Riverside scored the game's only run. Dickmann (24-5) threw a three-hitter but 
took her first loss since March 18. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Loyola Marymount d. Cal State Northridge, 15-6, 15-11, 15-12 -- The Matadors 
(11-20, 3-15) were swept for the first time since their Western Intercollegiate 
Volleyball Assn. opener 17 matches ago in a loss at Loyola Marymount. Outside 
hitter Bob Samuelson had 13 kills, but had a hitting percentage of only .091. 
</P>
