<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GTE Corp: The Stamford, Conn., firm's earnings rose to $329 million, up 15% 
from the 1988 quarter. Revenue rose 5% to $4.1 billion. Local telephone 
service, the company's major business, gained 7% in revenue to $3 billion. It 
said operating income rose only fractionally, to $689 million, because of rate 
actions by regulators in California and Texas. 
</P>
