<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARMY DISCIPLINES 27 FOR TRAINING METHODS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLUMBUS, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Army disciplined 27 noncommissioned and commissioned officers at Ft. 
Benning for mistreating recruits, a spokesman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The mistreatment, which occurred in February, sent 36 new soldiers to a 
military hospital, where doctors diagnosed them as suffering from a muscle 
deterioration condition brought on by excessive exercise. All but one of the 
recruits has returned to training, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
