<P>
A Christian Science couple was found guilty in Sarasota, Fla., of third-degree 
murder and felony child abuse in the death of their 7-year-old daughter Amy, 
who died at home in 1986 of diabetes after they relied on prayer for her 
recovery instead of seeking medical care. The six-member jury deliberated for 
