Christine, 38, guilty. The Hermansons used as their defense a 1975 Florida law 
that protects parents who withhold treatment from children if they are 
"legitimately practicing" religious beliefs. But the prosecution told jurors 
that Christian Science allows medical intervention when prayer has not worked. 
