<P>
SERVEN TO COACH NEWPORT HARBOR BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Serven said Tuesday he has been hired as boys' basketball coach at Newport 
Harbor High School. 
</P>
<P>
Serven, 28, replaces Jerry DeBusk, who resigned last month to become an 
assistant coach at Chapman College. 
</P>
<P>
Serven has coached at Newport Harbor for the past three seasons, two with the 
junior varsity and one with the sophomore team. He also has been a varsity 
assistant coach at Santiago, Arroyo and Bosco Tech high schools. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Meylor resigned as the Loara High School boys' basketball coach Tuesday, 
Athletic Director Ray Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
"Tom said he wanted to go back to school to earn his master's degree," Moore 
said. "He felt he couldn't do that and coach. He just didn't have enough time." 
</P>
<P>
Meylor has been the Saxons' coach for the past three seasons. Loara was 4-17 
overall and 2-8 in the Empire League last season. 
</P>
<P>
Meylor will remain at the school as a business teacher. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Wehren, a four-year varsity starter for Woodbridge High School's softball 
team and a shortstop on last year's Southern Section 2-A championship team has 
signed a letter of intent to attend San Jose State as a pitcher, her mother, 
Gail Wehren, said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Wehren is 7-4 this season with an 0.38 ERA and four shutouts, 45 strikeouts and 
four earned runs in 74 innings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
