<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Craig Takeover Considered: Yucaipa Capital Partners, a Claremont-based limited 
partnership, has said in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing that it 
may seek control of Craig Corp. Yucaipa said in the document that it may add to 
its 9.3% stake in Craig or sell all or part of that stock. The SEC statement 
also said Yucaipa may discuss possible corporate restructuring options with 
Craig. Executives at Los Angeles-based Craig, which owns 50% of the Stater 
Bros. supermarket company, had no immediate comment. Yucaipa filed the 
statement Friday. Craig stock closed at $38.50, up 50 cents Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
