<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John Charles Tighe, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A discussion on athletes in industry will be among the topics covered at a 
seminar on risk management in health, sponsored by insurance broker Fred S. 
James &amp; Co. of California. 
</P>
<P>
The Irvine brokerage said it is holding the seminar to show its clients and 
other employers that increased awareness of wellness can cut medical claims and 
worker compensation claims. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a matter of fact, but employers don't know what they can do," said Sally 
LeSage, a spokeswoman for James. Among the scheduled topics are accident 
prevention and health promotion. 
</P>
<P>
LeSage said 50 employers have said so far that they will attend the public 
seminar, which will be held at the Westin South Coast Plaza hotel in Costa 
Mesa. The seminar has a $10 fee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
