<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDCO RESEARCH EXTENDS RESEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Medco Research Inc. of Los Angeles secured from the University of Virginia 
Alumni Patents Foundation an extension of its exclusive right to research, 
develop and market Adenocard for $200,000, according to a Securities and 
Exchange Commission filing. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Medco has until March, 1992, to obtain Federal Drug 
Administration approval for Adenocard, an injectable acute treatment for 
supraventricular tachycardia. 
</P>
<P>
Medco manufactures pharmaceuticals and medical devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
