<HEADLINE>
<P>
INVESTORS REDUCE HOLDINGS IN UAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group led by LA Partners L.P. of New York, has reduced its stake in UAL 
Corp., the Chicago-based parent of United Airlines, from 5.51% to 4%, or 
849,435 common shares. 
</P>
<P>
The group, which also includes LA International Ltd., sold a total of 310,300 
UAL shares between March 31 and April 14 for from $117.25 to $120 each, 
according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Several principals in LA Partners, including Paul E. Tierney Jr., are also 
involved with Coniston Partners, the group bidding to acquire TW Services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
