<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV RATINGS; 
</P>
<P>
'ROSEANNE' CAN'T PULL ABC OUT OF THE CELLAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABC again had the top-rated show of the week in "Roseanne" but still came in 
third overall because of some low-rated weekend programming, figures from the 
A.C. Nielsen Co. showed Tuesday. NBC finished first for the 43rd week in a row, 
although there was nothing to cheer in the premieres of two new series, "Dream 
Street" (No. 42) and "The Jim Henson Hour" (No. 71). The latter shared the 
bottom rungs of the Nielsen ladder with such ABC offerings as "Moonlighting," 
"Great Circuses of the World" and "Men." The full list of ratings is on Page 8. 
</P>
<P>
* NBC doesn't have a "Lonesome Dove" on its hands in "Around the World in 80 
Days." The premiere of the three-part miniseries Sunday night finished third in 
its time period behind ABC's TV movie "A Deadly Silence" and CBS' TV movie 
"Love and Betrayal." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
