<P>
ROMANIAN SWIMMER ASKS ASYLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RENNES, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old Romanian swimmer who disappeared Monday just before her team 
returned to Bucharest after a weekend competition has asked for political 
asylum in France, police sources said today. 
</P>
<P>
Livia Copariu, who set short pool world's best times in the 50 and 100 meters 
freestyle in Romania earlier this month, disappeared after competing at an 
international event in Rennes. The sources said Copariu, who has been placed 
under police protection, indicated she wanted to rejoin her former trainer, 
Micha Micklaus, who now lives in West Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
